,"link":null},"annotations":{"bold":false,"italic":false,"strikethrough":false,"underline":false,"code":false,"color":"default"},"plain_text":"Uneven tire wear","href":null}],"color":"default"},"archived":false},{"object":"block","id":"35534d6d-7cea-81bf-8825-f2eeb19d96f2","parent":{"type":"page_id","page_id":"35534d6d-7cea-81de-9513-e203e9f3c1fc"},"created_time":"2026-05-03T22:01:00.000Z","last_edited_time":"2026-05-03T22:01:00.000Z","created_by":{"object":"user","id":"35534d6d-7cea-8179-8809-002768bc44c3"},"last_edited_by":{"object":"user","id":"35534d6d-7cea-8179-8809-002768bc44c3"},"has_children":false,"in_trash":false,"type":"paragraph","paragraph":{"rich_text":[{"type":"text","text":{"content":"Check if there are any uneven signs of wear on each tire. There could be an underlying issue that is causing premature wear due to the road condition or the application.","link":null},"annotations":{"bold":false,"italic":false,"strikethrough":false,"underline":false,"code":false,"color":"default"},"plain_text":"Check if there are any uneven signs of wear on each tire. There could be an underlying issue that is causing premature wear due to the road condition or the application.","href":null}],"icon":null,"color":"default"},"archived":false},{"object":"block","id":"35534d6d-7cea-81d8-b1c3-f7e49c602cce","parent":{"type":"page_id","page_id":"35534d6d-7cea-81de-9513-e203e9f3c1fc"},"created_time":"2026-05-03T22:01:00.000Z","last_edited_time":"2026-05-03T22:01:00.000Z","created_by":{"object":"user","id":"35534d6d-7cea-8179-8809-002768bc44c3"},"last_edited_by":{"object":"user","id":"35534d6d-7cea-8179-8809-002768bc44c3"},"has_children":false,"in_trash":false,"type":"paragraph","paragraph":{"rich_text":[{"type":"text","text":{"content":"       2. Air pressure","link":null},"annotations":{"bold":false,"italic":false,"strikethrough":false,"underline":false,"code":false,"color":"default"},"plain_text":"       2. Air pressure","href":null}],"icon":null,"color":"default"},"archived":false},{"object":"block","id":"35534d6d-7cea-81a4-966e-d0965b91cdde","parent":{"type":"page_id","page_id":"35534d6d-7cea-81de-9513-e203e9f3c1fc"},"created_time":"2026-05-03T22:01:00.000Z","last_edited_time":"2026-05-03T22:01:00.000Z","created_by":{"object":"user","id":"35534d6d-7cea-8179-8809-002768bc44c3"},"last_edited_by":{"object":"user","id":"35534d6d-7cea-8179-8809-002768bc44c3"},"has_children":false,"in_trash":false,"type":"paragraph","paragraph":{"rich_text":[{"type":"text","text":{"content":"Tires that aren’t filled to the proper pressure will wear out more quickly than tires filled to the correct PSI. Over inflation can also result in excessive tire wear.","link":null},"annotations":{"bold":false,"italic":false,"strikethrough":false,"underline":false,"code":false,"color":"default"},"plain_text":"Tires that aren’t filled to the proper pressure will wear out more quickly than tires filled to the correct PSI. Over inflation can also result in excessive tire wear.","href":null}],"icon":null,"color":"default"},"archived":false},{"object":"block","id":"35534d6d-7cea-8155-bab0-c3897ce8e742","parent":{"type":"page_id","page_id":"35534d6d-7cea-81de-9513-e203e9f3c1fc"},"created_time":"2026-05-03T22:01:00.000Z","last_edited_time":"2026-05-03T22:01:00.000Z","created_by":{"object":"user","id":"35534d6d-7cea-8179-8809-002768bc44c3"},"last_edited_by":{"object":"user","id":"35534d6d-7cea-8179-8809-002768bc44c3"},"has_children":false,"in_trash":false,"type":"paragraph","paragraph":{"rich_text":[{"type":"text","text":{"content":"       3. Load","link":null},"annotations":{"bold":false,"italic":false,"strikethrough":false,"underline":false,"code":false,"color":"default"},"plain_text":"       3. Load","href":null}],"icon":null,"color":"default"},"archived":false},{"object":"block","id":"35534d6d-7cea-8124-9780-e07ca724b3e1","parent":{"type":"page_id","page_id":"35534d6d-7cea-81de-9513-e203e9f3c1fc"},"created_time":"2026-05-03T22:01:00.000Z","last_edited_time":"2026-05-03T22:01:00.000Z","created_by":{"object":"user","id":"35534d6d-7cea-8179-8809-002768bc44c3"},"last_edited_by":{"object":"user","id":"35534d6d-7cea-8179-8809-002768bc44c3"},"has_children":false,"in_trash":false,"type":"paragraph","paragraph":{"rich_text":[{"type":"text","text":{"content":"While you don’t want to overload the lift truck, running the forklift without a load also shortens your tire life. Without a load on the forks, the counterweight presses down on the steer tires which causes them to wear more quickly.","link":null},"annotations":{"bold":false,"italic":false,"strikethrough":false,"underline":false,"code":false,"color":"default"},"plain_text":"While you don’t want to overload the lift truck, running the forklift without a load also shortens your tire life. Without a load on the forks, the counterweight presses down on the steer tires which causes them to wear more quickly.","href":null}],"icon":null,"color":"default"},"archived":false},{"object":"block","id":"35534d6d-7cea-81df-aebb-caf565226e87","parent":{"type":"page_id","page_id":"35534d6d-7cea-81de-9513-e203e9f3c1fc"},"created_time":"2026-05-03T22:01:00.000Z","last_edited_time":"2026-05-03T22:01:00.000Z","created_by":{"object":"user","id":"35534d6d-7cea-8179-8809-002768bc44c3"},"last_edited_by":{"object":"user","id":"35534d6d-7cea-8179-8809-002768bc44c3"},"has_children":false,"in_trash":false,"type":"image","image":{"caption":[],"type":"external","external":{"url":"https://maxamtire.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/did-you-know_forklift-safety-image.png"}},"archived":false},{"object":"block","id":"35534d6d-7cea-81a3-9618-d36c28cf0e33","parent":{"type":"page_id","page_id":"35534d6d-7cea-81de-9513-e203e9f3c1fc"},"created_time":"2026-05-03T22:01:00.000Z","last_edited_time":"2026-05-03T22:01:00.000Z","created_by":{"object":"user","id":"35534d6d-7cea-8179-8809-002768bc44c3"},"last_edited_by":{"object":"user","id":"35534d6d-7cea-8179-8809-002768bc44c3"},"has_children":false,"in_trash":false,"type":"paragraph","paragraph":{"rich_text":[{"type":"text","text":{"content":"After a tire has worn 40%, the forklift and the driver will absorb over 84% of the shock if it’s being run over a rough surface. The transmission must work much harder to turn the tires the same amount of rotation, which can result in a breakdown.","link":null},"annotations":{"bold":true,"italic":false,"strikethrough":false,"underline":false,"code":false,"color":"default"},"plain_text":"After a tire has worn 40%, the forklift and the driver will absorb over 84% of the shock if it’s being run over a rough surface. The transmission must work much harder to turn the tires the same amount of rotation, which can result in a breakdown.","href":null},{"type":"text","text":{"content":" Therefore, maintaining tires is an inexpensive way to keep your forklift and operator in good condition.","link":null},"annotations":{"bold":false,"italic":false,"strikethrough":false,"underline":false,"code":false,"color":"default"},"plain_text":" Therefore, maintaining tires is an inexpensive way to keep your forklift and operator in good condition.","href":null}],"icon":null,"color":"default"},"archived":false},{"object":"block","id":"35534d6d-7cea-813c-ab23-d481eb03197d","parent":{"type":"page_id","page_id":"35534d6d-7cea-81de-9513-e203e9f3c1fc"},"created_time":"2026-05-03T22:01:00.000Z","last_edited_time":"2026-05-03T22:01:00.000Z","created_by":{"object":"user","id":"35534d6d-7cea-8179-8809-002768bc44c3"},"last_edited_by":{"object":"user","id":"35534d6d-7cea-8179-8809-002768bc44c3"},"has_children":false,"in_trash":false,"type":"image","image":{"caption":[],"type":"external","external":{"url":"https://maxamtire.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/NFSD23-infographic.png"}},"archived":false},{"object":"block","id":"35534d6d-7cea-81e6-9282-d1d9b3a46531","parent":{"type":"page_id","page_id":"35534d6d-7cea-81de-9513-e203e9f3c1fc"},"created_time":"2026-05-03T22:01:00.000Z","last_edited_time":"2026-05-03T22:01:00.000Z","created_by":{"object":"u